<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 9301 contains definitions which pertain to this chapter only.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Clause (1) defines “Canadian registered pilot” as an individual registered as a pilot in Canada on the same basis as the United States.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Clause (2) defines “Great Lakes” as the five lakes plus their connecting and tributary waters, a certain part of the Saint Lawrence River, and adjacent ports.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Clause (3) defines “United States registered pilot” as an individual registered under regulations for competency under section 9303.</p>
